{"key":"processedPost-17860278","value":{"id":17860278,"first":17859592,"last":17863291,"when":1361764967,"utime":"02/25/13 06:02 AM","content":"You might want to get the basics down first.&nbsp; Brown rice flour is universally known as the fastest way to get from spores to fruits, bar none.&nbsp; In speed, it will outperform rice bran or any other substrate.<br />Minerals in bird seed and other grains do not impede colonization.&nbsp; We actually add minerals(gypsum) to our grains.&nbsp; Mg does impede colonization so we never use dolomite lime products.<br />It's a mistake to think in terms of 'nutrition' ala botany and apply it to fungi which have different requirements.&nbsp; For example the largest <i>P cubensis</i> mushrooms you'll ever see will be grown on straw which is one of the <i>least nutritious</i> substrates we have.&nbsp; Shiitake growers supplement their sawdust with a bit of rice, wheat or oat bran, but if we overdo it by even a small amount, they only form mutants and no real fruits.<br />RR","title":"Re: Seeking Participants for New Tek Development"}}